Package org.eclipse.uml.a2acsl.values

Interface Summary
Value Represents a generic value in the program.
 

Class Summary
FeatureValue Represents the value of a structural feature access Examples : obj.id, obj.tab -> at(i)
OpaqueValue Describes the value taken by the output of an Opaque Action
ReturnValue Represents a value returned by an operation call.
StringValue Represents a string value containing an expression expressed in OCL Examples: 10, x(parameter), v(local variable), obj.id(access)
 

Enum Summary
ReturnValue.ReturnType Describes types of ReturnValues : From an operation result or an OUT parameter
